requests.description: Updates the specified canned response by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

requests.description: This report shows you where you get your chats from. They can come from i.e. automatic invitations, manual invitations or the visitors can start the chats by themselves.

requests.name: Greetings
requests.description:
Returns the “greetings to chats to goals” conversion rates report.

displayed is the number of displayed greetings. accepted tells you how many chats resulted from these greetings. goals tells you how many goals resulted from these greetings.

requests.description:
Updates the specified goal by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

The GOAL_ID is obtained from the goals list.

requests.description: Shows the tickets that were rated during the specified period.

requests.description: Updates tags associated with the ticket.

requests.description: Shows the ratio of good to bad ratings for each operator.

requests.name: Chats response time
requests.description: The average amount of time it takes the agents to respond to a new message in a chat during a specified period.

requests.name: Availability
requests.description: Shows how long an agent (or a group or the whole account) was available for chatting during a specified period. When querying for one day, the results are shown in minutes per every hour, otherwise in hours for each day.

requests.name: Update chat tags
requests.description: This method updates the tags assigned to a chat.

requests.name: List all visitors
requests.description: Returns a list of the visitors on the pages with the tracking code installed.

requests.name: Tickets resolution time
requests.description: Shows the resolution time of the tickets that were solved during the specified period.

requests.name: Delete a tag
requests.description:
Deletes a tag from the chosen group. The agents will no longer be able to tag chats and tickets using this tag.

Deleting a tag will not remove it from the archived chats and tickets.

requests.name: Goals
requests.description: Shows the number of reached goals.

requests.name: Queued visitors
requests.description: Shows how many visitors waited in the queue and how many abandoned the queue or proceeded to chats

requests.name: Queue waiting times
requests.description: Shows the Minimum, Average and Maximum waiting time.

requests.name: Chatting time
requests.description: Shows how much time an agent (or a group) spent on chatting during a specified period. When querying for one day, the results are shown in minutes per every hour, otherwise in hours for each day.

requests.name: Mark a goal as successful
requests.description: The GOAL_ID is obtained from the goals list.

requests.name: Get status
requests.description: Returns the current LiveChat status. Available return values: online, offline.

requests.name: Update greeting
requests.description: Use this request to change the name or message of a greeting.

requests.name: Tickets first response time
requests.description: Shows the time of the first response to the tickets that were responded to for the first time during the specified period.

requests.name: Number of simultaneous chats
requests.description: This request shows the maximum number of concurrent chats that happened at the same hour on a particular day.

requests.name: Add custom visitor details
requests.description: Displays additional information about a visitor in LiveChat apps.

requests.description: Returns a single ticket item for the given TICKET_ID
